0001pt;text-align:center;&#10;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3A:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> Uroflowmetry showing poor flow with a Q max of 11 ml/sec.</span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%;\">3B:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%;\"> Urodynamic evaluation high pressure voiding with poorly compliant bladder.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;&#10;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:center;&#10;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"citation target=\"><b>Citation: </b> </span>Sekar H, Krishnamoorthy S, Kumaresan N (2020) Bilateral Spontaneous  Urinoma-A Common Condition due to Uncommon Cause. J Surg Urol 1:002. JSU-002.000002</p>', '', 'JSU-00299175.pdf ', 'SurgicalUrology49696.jpg ', '2020-01-10 21:24:16', '0', NULL);
